The paper deals with the analysis of neuronal simulators on complex networks, which suggests that it belongs to the sub-category of Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE). The use of the Equation-Free approach for multiscale computations and the focus on system-level tasks such as bifurcation and stability analysis suggest that it could also belong to the sub-category of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) or Modeling and Simulation (cs.MS). The examination of rare events and the consideration of network topology suggest that it could also belong to the sub-categories of Systems and Control (cs.SY) or Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science (cs.CE).
